The dates 310 sufficiently confirmed by the reference to Adrian VI as the new Pope, and by the coincidence 01 the two final petitions with those in Ep. 1276.

Peter Ruiz de la Mota († 0. 19 Sept. 1522) of Burgos was at this time one 01 , the leading personages in Charles' court. From being court-preacher to the Archduke Philip he entered Maximilian’s service and became Imperial Secretary and Councillor. In those early years, perhaps 0. 1506, he was introduced at Strasburg to Wimpfeling: for whom thenceforward he entertained high regard. In consequence Spiegel in 1514 dedicated to him Wimpfeling's autobiographical Ezpurqatio (see Ep. 224 introd.).
